name: A. L. York and G. Jackson, Jr., Assignees, Appellants, v. W. M. Hamer and Williams Holding Company, Appellees

judges: Terrell, C. J., and Whitfield and Buford, J. J., concur.
parties: A. L. York and G. Jackson, Jr., Assignees, Appellants, v. W. M. Hamer and Williams Holding Company, Appellees.

opinions.text:
Per Curiam.
This cause having heretofore been submitted. to the Court upon the transcript of the record of the orders herein, and briefs and argument of counsel for the respective parties, and the record having been seen and inspected, and the Court being now advised of its judgment to be given in the premises, it seems to the Court that there are no errors in the said orders; it is therefore, considered, ordered and adjudged by the Court that the said orders of the circuit court be, and the same are hereby, affirmed.
Terrell, C. J., and Whitfield and Buford, J. J., concur.
opinions.author: Per Curiam.

casebody.head_matter:
A. L. York and G. Jackson, Jr., Assignees, Appellants, v. W. M. Hamer and Williams Holding Company, Appellees.
Special Division A.
Decision filed January 5, 1931.
Bainum <b Bainum, for Appellants;
Dickinson & Dickinson, for Appellees.
